      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(nextcloud-talk): silently ignore non-message Talk events instead of returning 400",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nNextcloud Talk sends various event types (calls, system notifications, file shares) that may not have `object.type === \"Note\"` or `actor.type === \"Person\"`. The webhook handler's Zod schema was too strict — rejecting any payload that didn't match the exact message shape with a 400 \"Invalid payload format\" error.\n\nThis fix silently ignores non-matching payloads instead of returning 400, matching how other channel handlers gracefully handle unknown events.\n\nFixes #81566\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe `decodeWebhookCreateMessage` function returned `{ kind: \"invalid\" }` and wrote a 400 error for any payload that passed signature verification but failed the message schema check. Non-message Talk events (system notifications, call events, file shares) also pass signature verification but intentionally do not match the chat-message schema. The 400 response caused Nextcloud to log errors and could trigger retry loops.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNon-message Talk events are now silently acknowledged instead of returning 400. Message handling is unchanged — valid chat messages continue to be processed normally.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Test run**: `pnpm test extensions/nextcloud-talk --reporter=verbose`\n  - **15 test files passed, 92 tests passed, 0 failures**\n  - Key test: `returns 200 for schema-mismatch payloads after signature verification` — confirms non-message payloads receive 200 instead of 400\n  - All existing monitor replay, payload validation, auth rate limiting, and channel lifecycle tests pass unchanged\n\n```text\n Test Files  15 passed (15)\n      Tests  92 passed (92)\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Nextcloud Talk webhook handler returned HTTP 400 \"Invalid payload format\" for non-message Talk events (calls, system notifications, file shares) whose `object.type` is not `\"Note\"` or `actor.type` is not `\"Person\"`. The 400 caused Nextcloud to log errors and could trigger retry loops.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node v24, Linux x86_64\n- **Test framework**: Vitest\n- **Branch**: `fix/issue-81566-nextcloud-talk-400`\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\npnpm test extensions/nextcloud-talk --reporter=verbose\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\n Test Files  15 passed (15)\n      Tests  92 passed (92)\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: Non-message Talk events that pass signature verification but fail the chat-message schema check now return HTTP 200 with `{ status: \"ignored\" }` instead of HTTP 400. The key test `returns 200 for schema-mismatch payloads after signature verification` confirms the behavioral change. Valid chat messages continue to be processed normally with no regression.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live Nextcloud Talk server with real non-message events (incoming calls, system notifications, file share events). The fix is verified at the integration test level using recorded/replayed webhook payloads that exercise the same code paths.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`No` — non-message events were already ignored after the 400 was returned; now they are silently acknowledged)\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`No`)\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`No`)",
